        "author_association": "NONE",
        "body": "Animations are \"resources\" within Godot, I believe. I think that might be the reason why copy and paste results in an instance of that animation, not a duplicate copy by default. Though I absolutely agree with you: I don't think an instance is the expected result when a user performs a copy and paste operation. \r\nIn my opinion what is currently available should be called \"set as instance source\" (right now known as copy) and \"paste animation instance\" (right now known as paste), and then there should also be a proper copy and paste, which does not create an instance/link/reference to an already existing animation, but just copy all keys and values and past them someplace else. Ideally via Ctrl+C, Ctrl+V or right click context menu in addition to the pull down menu.",
